{
  "episode": "C:\\Bakcup_Asus\\interested_indian_pipeline\\ep01",
  "title": "Untitled Episode",
  "voice": "en-US-JennyNeural",
  "word_segments_file": "source_audio/narration_words.json",
  "scenes": [
    {
      "id": "SCENE-001",
      "image": "images/SCENE-001.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-001.mp3",
      "script": "So here's something I learned last week that I still can't quite believe.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 0.231,
      "whisperx_end": 3.452
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-002",
      "image": "images/SCENE-002.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-002.mp3",
      "script": "If the prime minister wants to dismiss a state government in India, they can't just, do it.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 4.512,
      "whisperx_end": 9.214
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-003",
      "image": "images/SCENE-003.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-003.mp3",
      "script": "Instead, the president has to send a formal letter to the governor,",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 10.294,
      "whisperx_end": 13.635
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-004",
      "image": "images/SCENE-004.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-004.mp3",
      "script": "who then has to politely inform the chief minister that their government no longer enjoys confidence, and could they perhaps consider stepping down?",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 13.895,
      "whisperx_end": 21.157
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-005",
      "image": "images/SCENE-005.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-005.mp3",
      "script": "It's like if your boss wanted to fire you but had to send your mom a recommendation that maybe you should quit.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 22.217,
      "whisperx_end": 27.239
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-006",
      "image": "images/SCENE-006.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-006.mp3",
      "script": "This is a real constitutional procedure.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-01",
      "whisperx_start": 28.319,
      "whisperx_end": 30.3
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-007",
      "image": "images/SCENE-007.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-007.mp3",
      "script": "It has happened 37 times since independence.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-01",
      "whisperx_start": 31.36,
      "whisperx_end": 33.821
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-008",
      "image": "images/SCENE-008.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-008.mp3",
      "script": "And I need to explain why it exists, because the story behind it is somehow more absurd than the process itself.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-01",
      "whisperx_start": 34.901,
      "whisperx_end": 40.583
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-009",
      "image": "images/SCENE-009.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-009.mp3",
      "script": "Let me start with what this actually is.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-02",
      "whisperx_start": 41.683,
      "whisperx_end": 43.484
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-010",
      "image": "images/SCENE-010.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-010.mp3",
      "script": "Article 356 of the Indian Constitution allows the President to impose what's called President's Rule on any State.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-02",
      "whisperx_start": 44.624,
      "whisperx_end": 51.166
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-011",
      "image": "images/SCENE-011.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-011.mp3",
      "script": "When this happens, the elected state government is suspended, the chief minister is out, and the state is run directly by the central government through the governor.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 52.226,
      "whisperx_end": 60.408
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-012",
      "image": "images/SCENE-012.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-012.mp3",
      "script": "On paper, this is supposed to be an emergency measure for when a state government literally cannot function,",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 61.488,
      "whisperx_end": 66.749
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-013",
      "image": "images/SCENE-013.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-013.mp3",
      "script": "like if there's a complete breakdown of law and order or the legislature is so fractured nobody can form a majority.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 67.05,
      "whisperx_end": 72.791
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-014",
      "image": "images/SCENE-014.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-014.mp3",
      "script": "In practice, it's been used 91 times between 1950 and 2023.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 73.888,
      "whisperx_end": 78.771
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-015",
      "image": "images/SCENE-015.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-015.mp3",
      "script": "91 For context, there have been 17 Lok Savas in that same period.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 79.912,
      "whisperx_end": 85.356
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-016",
      "image": "images/SCENE-016.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-016.mp3",
      "script": "We've had more presidents rule in positions than general elections.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 86.417,
      "whisperx_end": 89.599
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-017",
      "image": "images/SCENE-017.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-017.mp3",
      "script": "And here's the thing that made me go back and re-read the Constitution three times,",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 90.76,
      "whisperx_end": 94.682
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-018",
      "image": "images/SCENE-018.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-018.mp3",
      "script": "the actual wording of Article 356 never defines what breakdown of constitutional machinery means.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 95.022,
      "whisperx_end": 100.886
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-019",
      "image": "images/SCENE-019.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-019.mp3",
      "script": "It just says the president can impose it if they're satisfied that the state government can't function.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 102.047,
      "whisperx_end": 106.668
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-020",
      "image": "images/SCENE-020.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-020.mp3",
      "script": "Satisfied based on what?",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-03",
      "whisperx_start": 107.769,
      "whisperx_end": 109.029
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-021",
      "image": "images/SCENE-021.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-021.mp3",
      "script": "The constitution doesn't say.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-03",
      "whisperx_start": 110.09,
      "whisperx_end": 111.59
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-022",
      "image": "images/SCENE-022.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-022.mp3",
      "script": "Now before you think this is just states whining about the central government being mean to them, let me give you a few examples of how this has actually been used.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-03",
      "whisperx_start": 112.67,
      "whisperx_end": 120.653
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-023",
      "image": "images/SCENE-023.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-023.mp3",
      "script": "In 1959, the Central Congress government dismissed the Communist government in Kerala, a government that had won a clear majority in a free election.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 121.913,
      "whisperx_end": 130.238
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-024",
      "image": "images/SCENE-024.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-024.mp3",
      "script": "The official reason was law and order breakdown.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-04",
      "whisperx_start": 131.279,
      "whisperx_end": 133.56
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-025",
      "image": "images/SCENE-025.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-025.mp3",
      "script": "The real reason was that Kerala's education reforms were making the Congress party nervous.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-04",
      "whisperx_start": 134.561,
      "whisperx_end": 138.944
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-026",
      "image": "images/SCENE-026.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-026.mp3",
      "script": "In 1977, after the emergency ended and Janata Party won the centre, they immediately dismissed nine Congress state governments,",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 140.104,
      "whisperx_end": 147.792
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-027",
      "image": "images/SCENE-027.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-027.mp3",
      "script": "including Tamil Nadu and Punjab, even though those governments had perfectly functioning majorities.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 148.112,
      "whisperx_end": 153.258
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-028",
      "image": "images/SCENE-028.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-028.mp3",
      "script": "The stated reason this time was that those assemblies no longer reflected the will of the people because the national mood had changed.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 154.359,
      "whisperx_end": 160.901
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-029",
      "image": "images/SCENE-029.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-029.mp3",
      "script": "Which is not actually a constitutional justification, but here we are.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 161.961,
      "whisperx_end": 165.762
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-030",
      "image": "images/SCENE-030.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-030.mp3",
      "script": "The most brazen one might be Arunachal Pradesh in 2016.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 166.823,
      "whisperx_end": 170.544
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-031",
      "image": "images/SCENE-031.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-031.mp3",
      "script": "The Congress had a majority.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-05",
      "whisperx_start": 171.564,
      "whisperx_end": 172.885
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-032",
      "image": "images/SCENE-032.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-032.mp3",
      "script": "There was an internal party dispute about who should be chief minister.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-05",
      "whisperx_start": 173.925,
      "whisperx_end": 176.946
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-033",
      "image": "images/SCENE-033.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-033.mp3",
      "script": "The governor, using powers I didn't even know governors had, advanced the assembly session date on his own, then said the government had lost confidence because of this internal party mess.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 178.046,
      "whisperx_end": 187.834
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-034",
      "image": "images/SCENE-034.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-034.mp3",
      "script": "The center imposed president's rule.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-06",
      "whisperx_start": 188.915,
      "whisperx_end": 190.616
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-035",
      "image": "images/SCENE-035.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-035.mp3",
      "script": "The Supreme Court later said this was completely illegal and reversed it, but not before the central government had successfully helped engineer a floor-crossing operation.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-06",
      "whisperx_start": 191.637,
      "whisperx_end": 200.203
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-036",
      "image": "images/SCENE-036.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-036.mp3",
      "script": "The constitutional machinery had broken down, apparently, because politicians were arguing about who should lead them, which, I mean, that's just called politics.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 201.284,
      "whisperx_end": 210.327
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-037",
      "image": "images/SCENE-037.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-037.mp3",
      "script": "Here's where the choreography gets properly weird.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-07",
      "whisperx_start": 211.447,
      "whisperx_end": 213.708
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-038",
      "image": "images/SCENE-038.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-038.mp3",
      "script": "The president cannot impose president's rule on their own initiative.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-07",
      "whisperx_start": 214.708,
      "whisperx_end": 217.929
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-039",
      "image": "images/SCENE-039.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-039.mp3",
      "script": "They need a report from the governor saying things are broken.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 218.969,
      "whisperx_end": 221.591
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-040",
      "image": "images/SCENE-040.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-040.mp3",
      "script": "The governor is appointed by the president, on the advice of the prime minister.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 222.591,
      "whisperx_end": 226.373
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-041",
      "image": "images/SCENE-041.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-041.mp3",
      "script": "So the chain of command is, prime minister tells president who to appoint as governor,",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 227.454,
      "whisperx_end": 231.856
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-042",
      "image": "images/SCENE-042.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-042.mp3",
      "script": "governor sends report to president saying state government should be dismissed, president acts on that report and dismisses the government.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 232.156,
      "whisperx_end": 238.98
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-043",
      "image": "images/SCENE-043.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-043.mp3",
      "script": "It's constitutional buck passing as a formal procedure.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 240.061,
      "whisperx_end": 242.762
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-044",
      "image": "images/SCENE-044.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-044.mp3",
      "script": "And then there's the parliamentary approval bit.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-08",
      "whisperx_start": 243.963,
      "whisperx_end": 246.005
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-045",
      "image": "images/SCENE-045.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-045.mp3",
      "script": "After the president imposes president's rule, both houses of parliament have to approve it within two months.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-08",
      "whisperx_start": 247.086,
      "whisperx_end": 252.612
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-046",
      "image": "images/SCENE-046.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-046.mp3",
      "script": "If they don't, president's rule automatically lapses.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 253.753,
      "whisperx_end": 256.576
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-047",
      "image": "images/SCENE-047.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-047.mp3",
      "script": "But here's the thing, if the party in power at the center has a majority in parliament, which they obviously do because they're in power, then this approval is essentially automatic.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 257.657,
      "whisperx_end": 267.166
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-048",
      "image": "images/SCENE-048.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-048.mp3",
      "script": "It's not a real check.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-09",
      "whisperx_start": 268.287,
      "whisperx_end": 269.328
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-049",
      "image": "images/SCENE-049.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-049.mp3",
      "script": "It's a constitutional formality designed to look like accountability.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-09",
      "whisperx_start": 270.408,
      "whisperx_end": 273.67
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-050",
      "image": "images/SCENE-050.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-050.mp3",
      "script": "I know this sounds like boring constitutional procedure stuff, so let me tell you why this actually matters.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 274.75,
      "whisperx_end": 280.113
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-051",
      "image": "images/SCENE-051.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-051.mp3",
      "script": "In the 1970s and 80s, president's rule was imposed 36 times.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 281.234,
      "whisperx_end": 285.536
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-052",
      "image": "images/SCENE-052.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-052.mp3",
      "script": "That's an average of once every 10 months for two decades.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 286.656,
      "whisperx_end": 289.598
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-053",
      "image": "images/SCENE-053.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-053.mp3",
      "script": "It became the standard central government tactic for dealing with opposition-ruled states.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 290.718,
      "whisperx_end": 294.961
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-054",
      "image": "images/SCENE-054.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-054.mp3",
      "script": "Win an election in a state?",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-10",
      "whisperx_start": 296.062,
      "whisperx_end": 297.323
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-055",
      "image": "images/SCENE-055.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-055.mp3",
      "script": "Cool, the center will just dismiss your government six months later.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-10",
      "whisperx_start": 298.384,
      "whisperx_end": 301.626
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-056",
      "image": "images/SCENE-056.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-056.mp3",
      "script": "The Supreme Court finally got so tired of this in 1994 that they laid down guidelines in the S.R.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 302.687,
      "whisperx_end": 308.411
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-057",
      "image": "images/SCENE-057.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-057.mp3",
      "script": "Bahmy case saying you can't just impose president's rule because you feel like it, there has to be actual objective evidence of constitutional breakdown, and courts can review it.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 308.451,
      "whisperx_end": 317.777
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-058",
      "image": "images/SCENE-058.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-058.mp3",
      "script": "After Baumei, the frequency dropped.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-11",
      "whisperx_start": 318.878,
      "whisperx_end": 320.86
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-059",
      "image": "images/SCENE-059.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-059.mp3",
      "script": "Between 1994 and 2023, president's rule has been imposed 23 times, still a lot, but less cartoonishly frequent.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-11",
      "whisperx_start": 321.9,
      "whisperx_end": 330.387
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-060",
      "image": "images/SCENE-060.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-060.mp3",
      "script": "And several of those were genuinely for hung assemblies where no party could form a government, which is arguably what the provision was meant for in the first place.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 331.428,
      "whisperx_end": 339.354
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-061",
      "image": "images/SCENE-061.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-061.mp3",
      "script": "But the Baumei judgment created its own absurdity.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-12",
      "whisperx_start": 340.435,
      "whisperx_end": 342.877
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-062",
      "image": "images/SCENE-062.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-062.mp3",
      "script": "Now when the center wants to impose president's rule,",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-12",
      "whisperx_start": 343.959,
      "whisperx_end": 346.461
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-063",
      "image": "images/SCENE-063.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-063.mp3",
      "script": "the governor's report has to be very carefully worded to make it sound like objective constitutional breakdown rather than political convenience.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 346.801,
      "whisperx_end": 354.007
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-064",
      "image": "images/SCENE-064.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-064.mp3",
      "script": "So you get these incredibly elaborate reports listing things like rising incidence of communal tension or deteriorating law and",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 355.11,
      "whisperx_end": 361.937
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-065",
      "image": "images/SCENE-065.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-065.mp3",
      "script": "order situation with attached statistics that may or may not actually show deterioration depending on which baseline you use.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 362.017,
      "whisperx_end": 368.743
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-066",
      "image": "images/SCENE-066.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-066.mp3",
      "script": "It's like writing a Yelp review designed to survive legal scrutiny.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 369.845,
      "whisperx_end": 372.968
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-067",
      "image": "images/SCENE-067.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-067.mp3",
      "script": "The governor becomes a constitutional lawyer trying to draft around precedent.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 373.969,
      "whisperx_end": 377.812
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-068",
      "image": "images/SCENE-068.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-068.mp3",
      "script": "Here's my favorite part of this whole mess.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-13",
      "whisperx_start": 378.833,
      "whisperx_end": 380.674
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-069",
      "image": "images/SCENE-069.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-069.mp3",
      "script": "The governor, who is the central figure in this entire process, has no fixed term.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-13",
      "whisperx_start": 381.754,
      "whisperx_end": 386.416
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-070",
      "image": "images/SCENE-070.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-070.mp3",
      "script": "They serve at the pleasure of the president, which in practice means at the pleasure of the prime minister.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 387.437,
      "whisperx_end": 392.279
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-071",
      "image": "images/SCENE-071.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-071.mp3",
      "script": "So if a governor refuses to send a report recommending president's rule, the center can just replace them with someone who will.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 393.359,
      "whisperx_end": 399.742
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-072",
      "image": "images/SCENE-072.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-072.mp3",
      "script": "This happened in Tamil Nadu in 1991.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-14",
      "whisperx_start": 400.763,
      "whisperx_end": 402.443
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-073",
      "image": "images/SCENE-073.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-073.mp3",
      "script": "The governor refused to recommend President's rule.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-14",
      "whisperx_start": 404.284,
      "whisperx_end": 406.645
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-074",
      "image": "images/SCENE-074.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-074.mp3",
      "script": "The center removed him and appointed a new governor, who promptly sent the report.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-14",
      "whisperx_start": 407.685,
      "whisperx_end": 411.606
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-075",
      "image": "images/SCENE-075.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-075.mp3",
      "script": "The Supreme Court later said the dismissal was invalid, but again, not before the political damage was done.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 412.626,
      "whisperx_end": 418.347
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-076",
      "image": "images/SCENE-076.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-076.mp3",
      "script": "Now let me explain why the Constitution set it up this way, because the framers weren't idiots.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 419.408,
      "whisperx_end": 424.149
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-077",
      "image": "images/SCENE-077.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-077.mp3",
      "script": "The original logic goes back to the Government of India Act 1935, which the British used to govern colonial India.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 425.253,
      "whisperx_end": 432.076
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-078",
      "image": "images/SCENE-078.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-078.mp3",
      "script": "That Act had a similar provision called Section 93, which allowed the Governor-General to take over provinces if the local government failed.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 433.077,
      "whisperx_end": 440.48
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-079",
      "image": "images/SCENE-079.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-079.mp3",
      "script": "The Constitutional Assembly in 1949 debated whether to include something similar.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 441.5,
      "whisperx_end": 446.323
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-080",
      "image": "images/SCENE-080.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-080.mp3",
      "script": "B.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-15",
      "whisperx_start": 447.403,
      "whisperx_end": 447.543
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-081",
      "image": "images/SCENE-081.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-081.mp3",
      "script": "R.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-15",
      "whisperx_start": 447.663,
      "whisperx_end": 447.723
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-082",
      "image": "images/SCENE-082.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-082.mp3",
      "script": "Ambedkar, who chaired the drafting committee, explicitly warned that Article 356 should be a dead letter,",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-15",
      "whisperx_start": 447.783,
      "whisperx_end": 453.805
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-083",
      "image": "images/SCENE-083.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-083.mp3",
      "script": "meaning it should exist for genuine emergencies but never actually be used.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 454.205,
      "whisperx_end": 458.186
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-084",
      "image": "images/SCENE-084.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-084.mp3",
      "script": "He said, and I'm quoting here, I hope the president will take proper precautions before actually dismissing the ministry.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 459.266,
      "whisperx_end": 465.548
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-085",
      "image": "images/SCENE-085.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-085.mp3",
      "script": "The assumption was that the president would act as a neutral constitutional arbiter, not a party political figure.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 466.588,
      "whisperx_end": 472.17
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-086",
      "image": "images/SCENE-086.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-086.mp3",
      "script": "The assumption was that governors would be elder statesmen above partisan politics.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 473.251,
      "whisperx_end": 477.196
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-087",
      "image": "images/SCENE-087.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-087.mp3",
      "script": "The assumption was that Parliament would provide meaningful oversight.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 478.317,
      "whisperx_end": 481.421
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-088",
      "image": "images/SCENE-088.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-088.mp3",
      "script": "All three of those assumptions turned out to be wrong within a decade of independence.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 482.482,
      "whisperx_end": 486.247
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-089",
      "image": "images/SCENE-089.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-089.mp3",
      "script": "And here's the thing that genuinely bothers me about this, there's a weird constitutional imbalance baked in here.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 487.458,
      "whisperx_end": 493.06
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-090",
      "image": "images/SCENE-090.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-090.mp3",
      "script": "If a chief minister has a majority in the state assembly, they cannot be removed by a vote of no confidence unless MLAs actually cross the floor and vote them out.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 494.12,
      "whisperx_end": 502.684
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-091",
      "image": "images/SCENE-091.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-091.mp3",
      "script": "That's a high bar.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-16",
      "whisperx_start": 503.724,
      "whisperx_end": 504.604
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-092",
      "image": "images/SCENE-092.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-092.mp3",
      "script": "It requires public defection, horse trading, all the ugly but visible mechanics of democratic politics.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-16",
      "whisperx_start": 505.645,
      "whisperx_end": 511.367
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-093",
      "image": "images/SCENE-093.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-093.mp3",
      "script": "But Article 356 lets the center bypass all of that.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 512.447,
      "whisperx_end": 516.149
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-094",
      "image": "images/SCENE-094.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-094.mp3",
      "script": "The governor sends a report, the president signs an order, and the democratically elected government is gone.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 517.21,
      "whisperx_end": 522.753
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-095",
      "image": "images/SCENE-095.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-095.mp3",
      "script": "No floor test required.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-17",
      "whisperx_start": 523.794,
      "whisperx_end": 525.154
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-096",
      "image": "images/SCENE-096.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-096.mp3",
      "script": "No public vote.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-17",
      "whisperx_start": 526.195,
      "whisperx_end": 527.075
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-097",
      "image": "images/SCENE-097.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-097.mp3",
      "script": "Just executive action wrapped in constitutional language.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-17",
      "whisperx_start": 528.096,
      "whisperx_end": 531.118
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-098",
      "image": "images/SCENE-098.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-098.mp3",
      "script": "The counter-argument, which I should mention because some of you are already typing it,",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 532.19,
      "whisperx_end": 536.292
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-099",
      "image": "images/SCENE-099.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-099.mp3",
      "script": "is that without Article 356, there's no mechanism to deal with genuinely broken state governments.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 536.612,
      "whisperx_end": 542.295
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-100",
      "image": "images/SCENE-100.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-100.mp3",
      "script": "And that's fair.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-18",
      "whisperx_start": 543.396,
      "whisperx_end": 544.156
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-101",
      "image": "images/SCENE-101.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-101.mp3",
      "script": "In 1992, after Babri Masjid was demolished, the UP government had clearly failed to maintain law and order.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-18",
      "whisperx_start": 545.237,
      "whisperx_end": 552.1
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-102",
      "image": "images/SCENE-102.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-102.mp3",
      "script": "President's rule there was arguably justified.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-19",
      "whisperx_start": 553.12,
      "whisperx_end": 555.382
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-103",
      "image": "images/SCENE-103.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-103.mp3",
      "script": "In 2005, Bihar had a hung assembly and literally no combination of parties could form a majority, president's rule was the only option until fresh elections.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-19",
      "whisperx_start": 556.462,
      "whisperx_end": 565.628
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-104",
      "image": "images/SCENE-104.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-104.mp3",
      "script": "The provision isn't inherently illegitimate.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-20",
      "whisperx_start": 566.749,
      "whisperx_end": 568.871
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-105",
      "image": "images/SCENE-105.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-105.mp3",
      "script": "It's the frequency and context of its use that creates the problem.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-20",
      "whisperx_start": 569.931,
      "whisperx_end": 573.193
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-106",
      "image": "images/SCENE-106.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-106.mp3",
      "script": "But here's what I keep coming back to.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-21",
      "whisperx_start": 574.214,
      "whisperx_end": 575.915
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-107",
      "image": "images/SCENE-107.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-107.mp3",
      "script": "We have a federal system where states are supposed to have independent executive authority in their domains.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-21",
      "whisperx_start": 576.876,
      "whisperx_end": 581.879
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-108",
      "image": "images/SCENE-108.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-108.mp3",
      "script": "The whole point of federalism is that states aren't just administrative units of the center, they're autonomous political entities with their own elected governments.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 582.98,
      "whisperx_end": 590.805
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-109",
      "image": "images/SCENE-109.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-109.mp3",
      "script": "And yet we have a constitutional clause that lets the center suspend that autonomy with basically no advanced judicial review.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 591.925,
      "whisperx_end": 598.169
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-110",
      "image": "images/SCENE-110.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-110.mp3",
      "script": "The Supreme Court can reverse it afterwards, like they did in Arunachal, but by then the political crisis has already done its work.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 599.169,
      "whisperx_end": 606.194
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-111",
      "image": "images/SCENE-111.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-111.mp3",
      "script": "The current UPA-era Sarkaria Commission recommended in 1988 that Article 356 should only be used as a last resort,",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 607.194,
      "whisperx_end": 614.716
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-112",
      "image": "images/SCENE-112.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-112.mp3",
      "script": "and only when objective material shows constitutional breakdown.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 615.056,
      "whisperx_end": 618.256
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-113",
      "image": "images/SCENE-113.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-113.mp3",
      "script": "The National Commission to Review the Working of the Constitution in 2002 went further and suggested Article 356 should be amended to require a two-thirds majority in Parliament,",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 619.296,
      "whisperx_end": 629.439
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-114",
      "image": "images/SCENE-114.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-114.mp3",
      "script": "not just a simple majority, to approve President's rule.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 629.859,
      "whisperx_end": 632.859
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-115",
      "image": "images/SCENE-115.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-115.mp3",
      "script": "Neither recommendation has been implemented.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-22",
      "whisperx_start": 633.919,
      "whisperx_end": 635.96
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-116",
      "image": "images/SCENE-116.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-116.mp3",
      "script": "So where does this leave us?",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-22",
      "whisperx_start": 637.04,
      "whisperx_end": 638.141
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-117",
      "image": "images/SCENE-117.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-117.mp3",
      "script": "We have a constitutional provision designed for emergency use that became a routine political tool,",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-22",
      "whisperx_start": 639.262,
      "whisperx_end": 644.267
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-118",
      "image": "images/SCENE-118.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-118.mp3",
      "script": "then got partially restrained by courts, but still exists as this sort of Damocles hanging over every opposition-ruled state government.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 644.648,
      "whisperx_end": 651.674
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-119",
      "image": "images/SCENE-119.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-119.mp3",
      "script": "Governors have become the most powerful unelected officials in Indian federalism because they control access to this nuclear option.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 652.748,
      "whisperx_end": 659.59
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-120",
      "image": "images/SCENE-120.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-120.mp3",
      "script": "And the whole process is wrapped in this elaborate constitutional courtesy where the president must ask the governor to inform the chief minister,",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 660.63,
      "whisperx_end": 667.553
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-121",
      "image": "images/SCENE-121.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-121.mp3",
      "script": "as if adding procedural steps makes the power less blunt.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 667.933,
      "whisperx_end": 670.914
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-122",
      "image": "images/SCENE-122.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-122.mp3",
      "script": "I think the reason this bothers me is that it reveals a deep ambivalence in the Indian constitutional design about whether we actually trust federal democracy.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 671.974,
      "whisperx_end": 679.757
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-123",
      "image": "images/SCENE-123.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-123.mp3",
      "script": "If we trust it, why do we need a clause that lets the center overrule state voters?",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 680.817,
      "whisperx_end": 684.798
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-124",
      "image": "images/SCENE-124.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-124.mp3",
      "script": "If we don't trust it, why pretend we have federalism at all?",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 685.919,
      "whisperx_end": 688.9
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-125",
      "image": "images/SCENE-125.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-125.mp3",
      "script": "The Constitutional Assembly in 1949 couldn't resolve that tension, so they built Article 356 as a compromise,",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 689.94,
      "whisperx_end": 697.148
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-126",
      "image": "images/SCENE-126.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-126.mp3",
      "script": "a federal override switch that's supposed to exist but never be touched.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 697.468,
      "whisperx_end": 701.313
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-127",
      "image": "images/SCENE-127.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-127.mp3",
      "script": "Except we've touched it 91 times.",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-23",
      "whisperx_start": 702.414,
      "whisperx_end": 703.635
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-128",
      "image": "images/SCENE-128.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-128.mp3",
      "script": "And so we're left with this, a constitutional procedure where the president asks the governor to ask the chief minister to maybe resign,",
      "scene_type": "grouped",
      "visual_group_id": "group-23",
      "whisperx_start": 705.437,
      "whisperx_end": 712.343
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-129",
      "image": "images/SCENE-129.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-129.mp3",
      "script": "because formally acknowledging that the center can just fire state governments would make the whole federal structure look like theater.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 712.704,
      "whisperx_end": 718.809
    },
    {
      "id": "SCENE-130",
      "image": "images/SCENE-130.png",
      "audio": "audio/SCENE-130.mp3",
      "script": "Which, depending on how you count Article 356 impositions, it sort of already is.",
      "scene_type": "standalone",
      "visual_group_id": null,
      "whisperx_start": 719.89,
      "whisperx_end": 725.055
    }
  ]
}